As Muslims all over the world celebrates the end of 2022 Ramadan, on Monday the Chairman of FCT Golf Association, Engr Oladapo Olaide mohd’kabir, has congratulated Muslims, particularly his board members, officials, coaches, players and stakeholders. According to the statement signed by the FCT golf boss on Monday, Oladapo rejoiced with Muslim and enjoined them to remain steadfast in their prayers to All Mighty Allah to intervene in the country’s challenges, especially in forthcoming elections. “On behalf of my family and assocation, I heartily congratulate all Nigerians and Happy Eid-el-Fitr to all our Muslim brothers and sisters. As we celebrate the festivities, May All Mighty Allah accept our du’as as an act of ibadah Amin ”. “May this festivity push peace to transcend the earth, let light brighten up the Nigeria and grow hope to every Muslim’s heart. let us do more in sacrificing for others, so that the nation can be blessed with rewards for patriotic and selfless efforts,” he said. “As we celebrate, I also urge us to remember the poor and the needy in our society”. Oladapo however, used the opportunity to call on critical stakeholders to partner with the FCT golf association in making the sports a household name in the nation’s capital.